cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new notion of margin for deep models and analyzes its relationship with generalization. It also presents a training algorithm for increasing the margin and demonstrates its effectiveness in improving test performance. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks and the proposed margin can be applied to improve the generalization and robustness of these models. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI and the proposed margin and training algorithm can be applied to improve the performance of various AI applications. 

It may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper presents the first direct analysis of robust test error for deep networks, which is relevant to the security and robustness of these models. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper proposes a new notion of margin and a training algorithm for deep neural networks.
